# Forte Package Content License

The content in this directory tree (`packages/`) — songs, albums, blocks,
instruments, effects and recorded assets, in source form and as built
artifacts (.fortesong) — is licensed under:

  Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International
  (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

In plain language, for this ecosystem:

- **You may**: listen, learn, fork, remix, and redistribute the SOURCE and
  your derivative works — with attribution, under this same license, for
  non-commercial purposes. This is the point of Forte: transparent,
  forkable music.
- **You may not**: render this content (or derivatives of it) to audio
  files — WAV, MP3, streams, or any other bounced form — and commercially
  exploit that audio (sales, streaming monetization, sync licensing, paid
  performances of the recordings, NFT or dataset sales) without the
  explicit permission of the rights holder(s) recorded in the content's
  lineage.
- **Rights holders keep everything**: the original authors may license
  their own work commercially on any terms, independently of this license.
- Recorded assets (.frec) additionally carry provenance metadata; the
  performer's rights recorded there are not waived by this license.

The Forte SOFTWARE (crates/, web/, editor/, scripts/, docs/) is separately
licensed under the MIT License — see /LICENSE. This file governs only the
content under packages/.

This summary is not a substitute for the license text. If you need
commercial rights, contact the package author (see the package's meta and
lineage for attribution).
